    69	## Notes
    70	
    71	### Transaction Structure & Numbering (REQ-001 through REQ-005)
    72	- **Change Management Critical**: "This is like the one thing during discovery that people get tripped up on"
    73	- **Mitigation**: Project number stays consistent; global search; hyperlinked records; recent transactions dialog
    74	- **Training Focus**: Search by project, not order number; email subject lines reference project
    75	- **Timeline**: "Kleenex may be required, but we should be able to wipe our tears pretty quickly"
    76	
    77	### Customer PO Tracking (REQ-016, REQ-017, REQ-018)
    78	- **Business Driver**: Bank reporting requirement; payment delay risk mitigation
    79	- **Complexity**: Multiple POs per project; change orders; blanket POs
    80	- **Follow-Up**: Separate design session scheduled
    81	- **Competitive Advantage**: "Anything that we can do to make us look like we're easy to do business with"
    82	
    83	### Approval Workflows (REQ-020 through REQ-026)
    84	- **Current Rules Well-Defined**: Clear thresholds and routing
    85	- **Key Approvers**: Shannon ($25K, missing requirements); Matt (missing requirements, erosion)
    86	- **Purpose Beyond Control**: Training opportunity; problem-solving expertise
    87	- **Budget**: Up to 10 rules configured
    88	- **Action Item**: Shannon to document approval workflow flowchart
    89	
    90	### Tax Management (REQ-011, REQ-012, REQ-013)
    91	- **Government Orders**: 20% of business
    92	- **Miller Knoll Policy Conflict**: Warehouse tax vs. final destination tax
    93	- **Pain Point**: "Every tax person we've ever talked to in the entire 80 years of our existence in business, we have taxed to final destination"
    94	- **Reputational Risk**: "Government frustrated with KBM Hoag but 'we have no control over anything'"
    95	- **Volume**: ~$1M direct bill annually (1% of revenue)
    96	
    97	### Template Management (REQ-027 through REQ-030)
    98	- **Major Benefit**: Self-service eliminates vendor billable hours
    99	- **Kipp Ownership**: Strong design owner; pride in 5-year-old templates
   100	- **Current Pain**: "That's insane" - paying for simple changes
   101	- **Vendor POs**: "Shitstorm of information" - redesign opportunity
   102	- **Action Items**: Kipp to provide all templates; GSI to recreate
   103	
   104	### Order Types & Volume (REQ-031 through REQ-034)
   105	- **Intermarket Outbound**: Thousands annually; Shannon's primary workload (8-10/day)
   106	- **Government**: 20% of business
   107	- **Direct Bill**: ~$1M annually (1% of revenue)
   108	- **Intermarket Pain Point**: Setting up dealers as both vendor AND customer first time
   109	
   110	### Integrations (REQ-039 through REQ-042)
   111	- **ServiceNet**: Confirmed integration plan
   112	- **ServiceTime**: Critical for Shannon's thousands of intermarket orders
   113	- **Coupa**: Optional automation; Shannon's volume may justify
   114	- **Quote Tool**: Standard Miller Knoll integration
   115	
   116	### Tiered Pricing Challenge (REQ-043)
   117	- **Major Business Issue**: Installation strategy conflicts with pricing optimization
   118	- **Current Problem**: Split POs lose tiered discounts despite qualifying at project level
   119	- **Impact**: GP erosion on large multi-order projects
   120	- **Solution Path**: Escalation to Dustin (Miller Knoll product owner)
   121	- **Industry Impact**: "Other manufacturers and dealers that have the same challenge"
   122	- **Status**: FUTURE - pending Miller Knoll decision
